			<p class="post-day">19</p>
			<p class="post-year">2003</p>				
		</div>

		The Broadband Industry Group, a coalition of ISPs in the UK, has released a report suggesting that widespread competitive provision of broadband would add &#8356;22 billion (about $40 billion) to the British economy by 2015.
		
